    {
      "number": 7,
      "id": "I_kwDOK0CwpM5_Mdf7",
      "title": "Packets discard and Impact on Quality of experience",
      "url": "https://github.com/danwing/metadata/issues/7",
      "state": "OPEN",
      "author": "boucadair",
      "authorAssociation": "COLLABORATOR",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "FWIW, https://dspace.mit.edu/handle/1721.1/99941 revealed that: \"63% of the external communication made by top-popular free Android applications from Google Play has no effect on the user-observable application functionality\"\r\n\r\nMay be cited as an example of packets  that may be tagged as \"may-discard\".\r\n\r\n\r\n",
      "createdAt": "2024-02-14T10:05:03Z",
      "updatedAt": "2024-02-14T19:41:46Z",
      "closedAt": null,
      "comments": [
        {
          "author": "danwing",
          "authorAssociation": "OWNER",
          "body": "Based on the abstract (as I can't seem to access the paper itself), it seems to have analyzed **blocking** some communications from apps -- likely to advertising servers or to other non-primary servers, and said that most apps continued working fine when that communication was blocked.\r\n",
          "createdAt": "2024-02-14T19:41:45Z",
          "updatedAt": "2024-02-14T19:41:45Z"
        }
      ]
    }
